In a small bowl, soak raisins in hot water for 10 minutes until plump. Drain and set aside. Whisk together mayonnaise, curry powder, and lemon juice until smooth. Stir in scallions, raisins, and chicken. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in scallions, raisins, and chicken. Season with salt and pepper. Line two plates with spinach leaves and mound equal amounts of salad on each plate.